President Obama has issued a statement welcoming France's decision to fully reintegrate into NATO's military structure. He praises French President Nicolas Sarkozy's leadership and emphasizes that France's participation will contribute to a stronger Alliance and Europe. The statement also highlights the importance of close cooperation with Allies and partners in overcoming challenges. President Obama expresses his anticipation for discussing ways to ensure the strengthened Alliance, with France as a full participant, remains significant in the 21st century.